.TH BCA-OPS 1  "big-code-analysis 0.1.0" "big-code-analysis Manual"
.SH NAME
bca\-ops \- Extract per\-file operands and operators
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbca\-ops\fR [\fB\-O\fR|\fB\-\-output\-format\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-\-pretty\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Extract per\-file operands and operators
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-O\fR, \fB\-\-output\-format\fR \fI<OUTPUT_FORMAT>\fR
Output format
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
cbor
.IP \(bu 2
csv
.IP \(bu 2
json
.IP \(bu 2
toml
.IP \(bu 2
yaml
.RE
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Output directory. Filenames mirror input paths plus the format extension. Stdout if omitted (CBOR requires this flag)
.TP
\fB\-\-pretty\fR
Pretty\-print JSON / TOML output
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
